UNDIAGNOSED DEATHS - NIGERIA (02): (KANO) REQUEST FOR INFORMATION RESPONSES, RELATION TO COVID-19
*************************************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[A request for information about recent undiagnosed deaths in Kano State, Nigeria, was sent to the EpiCore Surveillance Project volunteers based in Nigeria. ProMED-mail is grateful for the following responses. - Mod.TY]

[1]
Date: Wed 10 Jun 2020 14:34
Source: EpiCore Global Surveillance Project member [edited]


Thanks for the RFI. What was initially regarded as mysterious wholesale deaths in Kano has been confirmed to be related to COVID-19. Even when there were controversial reports from government quarters, and the deaths conflated with malaria and meningitis, many health professionals, in the trenches, that I spoke with were unequivocal in their conclusions that this is caused by COVID-19. Many of the victims were reported to be above 60 and generally have respiratory distress as a core symptom, among others, which is not consistent with malarial and meningitis symptoms. Thankfully, the Minister of Health, Osagie Ehanire, has now confirmed, after initial tentativeness, that more than 60% of the deaths could be linked to COVID-19.

--
Communicated by:
EpiCore Global Surveillance Project member
<promed@promedmail.org>

******
[2]
Date: Thu 11 Jun 2020 06:53
Source: EpiCore Global Surveillance Project member [edited]


It is true that over 1000 deaths were recorded in Kano within the space of 3 weeks in April 2020. What was common among those that died were underlying chronic diseases. There were 3 bodies tested that were positive [presumably for SARS-CoV-2 virus]. Government has set up a committee to investigate the cause of the deaths. Outcome of the investigation is not yet known.

--
Communicated by:
EpiCore Global Surveillance Project member
<promed@promedmail.org>

******
[3]
Date: Fri 12 Jun 2020 06:11
Source: EpiCore Global Surveillance Project member [edited]


Follow-up:
- The federal government yesterday linked the death of about 587 out of the 979 people who died under controversial circumstances in Kano State in April [2020] to COVID-19. The figure represents 60% of the fatality data.

Speaking yesterday [11 Jun 2020] on the report of the federal government's fact-finding team sent to Kano State to investigate the strange deaths in the state, the Minister of Health, Dr. Osagie Ehanire, told journalists during the briefing by the Presidential Task Force on COVID-19 in Abuja that the final report showed that a total of 979 deaths were recorded in 8 municipal councils in the state at the rate of 43 deaths per day.
https://allafrica.com/stories/202006090577.html

- [Video] Federal Government confirms COVID-19 behind 60% mysterious deaths in Kano
https://youtu.be/S4I5MQKX10c

The above resources contain links to official government responses to the "mysterious deaths" reported in Kano.

