Communicated by:
EpiCore Global Surveillance Project member

[ProMED thanks the EpiCore network for comments relating to undiagnosed deaths in Kano State, Nigeria. All the above EpiCore reports confirm that there were hundreds of deaths in Kano State, peaking in April [2020] but continuing on for several weeks. The 1st EpiCore response indicates that the previously reported approximate 40% of deaths not attributed to SARS-CoV-2 virus infections were, in fact, due to that virus, but complicated by co-morbidities that contributed to their deaths. That many SARS-CoV-2 deaths implies that an epidemic of this virus occurred in the population, perhaps with well over 1000 infected individuals who did not die. It is not clear how many of the fatal cases were laboratory tested for SARS-CoV-2 virus or other pathogens. The individuals who died at home doubtless were not tested. - Mod.TY

